docs.lead_paragraph: AFTER a long existence the New York Milk Committee, headed by Mrs. Borden Harriman, has passed out of existence, satisfied that the work for which it was organized, has been accomplished. This work was the solution of the city's milk problem.

headline.main: CENTRALIZED STATE CONTROL OF MILK SUPPLY IS URGED; Dr. Charles E. North, Telling of the Effective Work of the New York Milk Committee, Says That the Cities Alone Can Never Handle the Situation Adequately.
